---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const lastUpdated = "19 February 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Terms of Service"
    description="Terms of Service for Swift Support Solutions - governing the use of our business consulting, financial advisory, accounting, and support services in Nepal."
>
    <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white">
        <div class="container py-12">
            <div class="max-w-2xl">
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
                <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">
                    Last updated: {lastUpdated}
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="container">
            <div
                class="max-w-3xl mx-auto"
                style="line-height:1.8; color:#334155; font-size:0.875rem;"
            >
                <div
                    class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8 text-sm text-amber-800"
                >
                    <strong>Governing Law:</strong> These Terms of Service are governed
                    by the laws of Nepal, including the <strong
                        >Muluki Civil Code 2074</strong
                    >, the <strong>Companies Act 2063</strong>, and other
                    applicable legislation. By engaging our services, you agree
                    to these Terms.
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    1. Parties
                </h2>
                <p>
                    These Terms constitute a binding agreement between <strong
                        >Swift Support Solutions Pvt. Ltd.</strong
                    > ("Company", "we", "us"), registered under the Companies Act
                    2063, Nepal, and you ("Client"), the individual or entity engaging
                    our services.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    2. Services
                </h2>
                <p>The Company provides professional services including:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
                    <li>Business Consultation</li>
                    <li>Business Financial Advisory</li>
                    <li>Events Management</li>
                    <li>Accounting & Bookkeeping (per NFRS/NAS standards)</li>
                    <li>Tax, VAT & Audit Support (IRD-registered)</li>
                    <li>Fundraising Solutions</li>
                    <li>Marketing & Branding</li>
                    <li>Project Management</li>
                    <li>Business Development</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Specific scope, deliverables, and timelines are agreed upon
                    in writing before each engagement commences.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    3. Engagement & Quotation
                </h2>
                <p>
                    All engagements begin with a written proposal or service
                    agreement specifying scope, fees, timeline, and
                    deliverables. No work commences until the Client has
                    accepted the proposal in writing or electronically. The
                    Company reserves the right to amend proposals if scope
                    changes materially.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    4. Fees & Payment
                </h2>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
                    <li>
                        All fees are quoted in Nepali Rupees (NPR) unless
                        otherwise agreed.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Invoices are payable within <strong>15 days</strong> of issuance
                        unless otherwise stated.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Late payments attract interest at the rate applicable
                        under the Muluki Civil Code 2074.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Applicable taxes (e.g. VAT at 13% per the Value Added
                        Tax Act 2052) will be added where required.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Professional Tax Deducted at Source (TDS) obligations of
                        the Client remain the Client's responsibility per the
                        Income Tax Act 2058.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    5. Client Responsibilities
                </h2>
                <p>The Client agrees to:</p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
                    <li>
                        Provide accurate, complete, and timely information
                        required for service delivery
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Obtain necessary approvals or authorisations before the
                        Company files on their behalf with IRD, OCR, or other
                        authorities
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Review and approve deliverables within agreed timelines
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Maintain confidentiality of any proprietary tools or
                        templates shared by the Company
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    6. Intellectual Property
                </h2>
                <p>
                    All methodologies, templates, and proprietary tools
                    developed by the Company remain the Company's intellectual
                    property. Client-specific deliverables are transferred to
                    the Client upon full payment. Neither party may use the
                    other's name or brand without prior written consent.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    7. Confidentiality
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Both parties agree to maintain strict confidentiality of all
                    business, financial, and personal information shared during
                    the engagement. This obligation survives the termination of
                    services for a period of <strong>3 years</strong>.
                    Disclosure is permitted only as required by Nepal law or
                    with prior written consent.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    8. Limitation of Liability
                </h2>
                <p>
                    The Company's liability for any claim arising from services
                    provided shall not exceed the total fees paid by the Client
                    in the 3 months preceding the claim. The Company is not
                    liable for losses arising from inaccurate or incomplete
                    information provided by the Client, or for decisions made by
                    the Client based on our advice without due consideration of
                    their specific circumstances.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Nothing in these Terms limits liability for gross
                    negligence, wilful misconduct, or fraud.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    9. Termination
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Either party may terminate an engagement by providing <strong
                        >14 days' written notice</strong
                    >. The Client remains liable for fees for work completed up
                    to the termination date. The Company may terminate
                    immediately if the Client engages in illegal activities,
                    withholds payment beyond 30 days, or provides materially
                    false information.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    10. Dispute Resolution
                </h2>
                <p>
                    In the event of a dispute, both parties agree to first
                    attempt resolution through good-faith negotiation within 30
                    days. If unresolved, disputes shall be referred to mediation
                    under Nepal's Arbitration Act 2055 before proceeding to
                    litigation. The courts of Kathmandu District shall have
                    exclusive jurisdiction.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    11. Amendments
                </h2>
                <p>
                    The Company may update these Terms from time to time.
                    Continued use of services after notification of revised
                    Terms constitutes acceptance. Clients will be notified of
                    material changes by email or website notice.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-3">
                    12. Contact
                </h2>
                <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-5 border border-slate-100">
                    <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900">
                        Swift Support Solutions Pvt. Ltd.
                    </p>
                    <p>Kathmandu, Bagmati Province, Nepal</p>
                    <p>
                        Email: <a
                            href="mailto:legal@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np"
                            class="text-amber-600 hover:underline"
                            >legal@swiftsupportsolutions.com.np</a
                        >
                    </p>
                    <p>Registered under Companies Act 2063, Nepal</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
